speech.p:
and in this Resolution 'the prescribed limits' means—


(a) the limit of £1,000 million imposed by the said Act of the present Session on the aggregate amount outstanding, otherwise than by way of interest, in respect of—


(i) the general external borrowing (as defined in the Act) of the National Enterprise Board and their wholly owned subsidiaries;

(ii) sums issued by the Treasury in fulfilment of guarantees in respect of sums borrowed by the Board from a person other than the Secretary of State;

(iii) sums paid to the Board as public dividend capital (as defined in the said Act); and

(iv) loans guaranteed by the Board othewise than in the exercise of powers conferred on the Secretary of State by sections 7 and 8 of the Industry Act 1972 and exercisable by the Board by virtue of the said Act of the present Session; and


(b) the limit of £1,800 million imposed by virtue of the said Act of the present Session on liabilities of the Secretary of State under guarantees given by him under section 10 of the Industry Act 1972 and section 7 of the Shipbuilding Industry Act 1967;
